==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scutate
<hw>Scu"tate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>scutatus</ets> armed with a shield, from <ets>scutum</ets> a
shield.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Buckler-shaped; round or nearly
round.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Protected or covered by bony or
horny plates, or large scales.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scutch</ent>⟦br⟧
